<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1921-09-15T11:35:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1921-09-15T11:35:00-05:00" n="579" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d579">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">891.51/230: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Persia</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Engert</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Teheran</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-09-15T20:00:00+03:25"><hi rend="italic">September 15,
                                        1921—8 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received September 16—5:53
                                p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>57. The Shah sent for me this afternoon and expressed the hope that now
                            that the British financial advisers had definitely severed their
                            connection with the Persian Government it might be possible to obtain
                            Americans to take their places. His Majesty then reiterated some of the
                            statements reported in the Legation’s 35, June 21, 4 p.m.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Engert</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>